@NODE intro.fb
@TITLE "Introduction"
@SMARTWRAP
@WORDWRAP
With ForceBorder you can permanently change the WBor??? fields in
the Screen structure of the Workbench screen.


What its good for ? Well, just open the "Execute command" requester
of the workbench or any other Window. Now compare the thickness of
the borders; the Bottomborder is 2 pixels and the left/right borders
are 4.


Wouldn't it be nice to have the bottom border also set to 4 pixels ?
Well, then you need this tool.
@{CODE}
@ENDNODE

@NODE install.fb
@TITLE "Installation"
@SMARTWRAP
@WORDWRAP
Just copy the binary somewhere into your command path (i.e. C:) and that's it!
Then edit your S:user-startup file and these lines to it:
@{CODE}
;BEGIN ForceBorder
run <>NIL: ForceBorder BOTTOM=4 QUIET
;END ForceBorder
@ENDNODE

@NODE usage.fb
@TITLE "Usage"
@SMARTWRAP
@WORDWRAP
@{CODE}
This is the CLI template: LEFT/N,RIGHT/N,TOP/N,BOTTOM/N

@{B}LEFT/RIGHT/TOP/BOTTOM@{UB}
	purpose:  change the named border field to a new value, i.e. BOTTOM=4
	default:  the default is no change
	cave-at:  it is not wise to change the TOP field !

@{B}QUIET@{UB}
	purpose:  hide the copyright message
	default:  show the copyright message
@ENDNODE

@NODE caveats.fb
@TITLE "Caveats"
@SMARTWRAP
@WORDWRAP
it is not wise to change the TOP field !


It has been reported that this tool sometimes conflicts
with other tools that change the border; this means it
does nothing!
@{CODE}
@ENDNODE

